URL: https://www2.swift.com/mystandards/#/mp/mx/_kijaUKEYEeuB-v2uhrZqSw/_rz7AJZ5FEeyNX8SYmSuaLA
Description: FedNow Service Scope

A FedNow broadcast is the message the FedNow Service uses to notify FedNow participants of a FedNow Service or a FedNow participant event.

FedNow Service Usage

The FedNow broadcast is used to provide information about the FedNow Service operations such as a FedNow funds-transfer business day extension or rollover, a change in a transaction limit, the availability of new FedNow Service public keys, or any ad hoc information related to the FedNow Service.

The FedNow broadcast is also used to relay a FedNow participant's operational status to all FedNow participants, i.e., a participant sign-on or sign-off.

The FedNow Service will also use the FedNow broadcast to inform an individual FedNow participant that it has been reactivated after a previous suspension.
